    <text>
        <body>                       
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="cww.01005.001.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="petition" subtype="handwritten" corresp="#rg21">                
                
                <div2 type="document" subtype="handwritten">
                    
                    <opener>
                        <salute>To <persName>John A. Smith</persName> <choice><abbr>Esq.</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice> Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</salute>
                        <salute>Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    
                    <p><persName>J. Thomas Davis</persName> of <placeName>Georgetown D.C.</placeName> having claim to the service or labor of the undersigned, and having refused or failed to file in your office the statement or schedule provided for in the 9th section of the act of Congress, entitled "An act for the release of certain persons held to service or labor in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>" Approved <date when="1862-04-16">16th April 1862</date>.</p>
                    <p>You will please file the annexed schedule in pursuance of an act supplementary to the above recited act approved <date when="1862-07-12">12 July 1862</date>. The undersigned resided in the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName> before and at the time of the passage of said supplemental act with said owners consent.</p>
                    <table>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Name</cell>
                            <cell>Sex</cell>
                            <cell>Age</cell>
                            <cell>Description</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row rend="handwritten">
                            <cell><persName>Mary Bell</persName></cell>
                            <cell>female</cell>
                            <cell>nine <choice><abbr>yrs</abbr><expan>years</expan></choice></cell>
                            <cell>dark color</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                    
                    <closer>
                        <signed>her X mark <persName>Mary Bell</persName></signed><lb/>
                        Witness
                        <signed><persName>J. M. Hanson</persName></signed>
                    </closer>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="cww.01005.002.jpg"/>
                
                <div2 type="cover" subtype="handwritten">
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Paid 50 <choice><abbr>cts</abbr><expan>cents</expan></choice></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab><persName>Mary Bell</persName></ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Recorded in Manumission Record No. 2 folio 95</ab>
                    </div3>
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <ab>Filed <date when="1862-09-03">3d Septr 1862</date></ab>
                    </div3>  
                    
                    <div3 type="section">
                        <p>The Commissioners, satisfied from the testimony of <persName>Henry C. Thomas</persName> &#38; <persName>Lucy Berry</persName> of the truth of the within statement order the same be so reported to the Clerk of the Circuit Court of the <placeName>District of Columbia</placeName>.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <dateline><date when="1862-09-03">Sept. 3, 1862</date></dateline>
                            <signed><persName>Wm. R. Woodward</persName><lb/>
                                Clerk to Commissioners</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div3>
                </div2>
            </div1>
               
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf002r" facs="cww.01005.003.jpg"/>
            <div1 type="evidence" corresp="#rg217" subtype="handwritten">
                <dateline><date when="1862-09-03">Sept 3 1862</date></dateline>
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><persName>Mary Bell</persName></ab>
                    <ab><choice><abbr>Servt</abbr><expan>Servant</expan></choice> of <persName>J Thomas Davis</persName></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Henry C. Thomas</persName>, summoned. I know the servant <persName>Mary</persName>, daughter of my father's <choice><abbr>servt</abbr><expan>servant</expan></choice>. I believe she belonged to  <persName>J Thomas Davis</persName> of <placeName>Georgetown DC</placeName>. I do not know whether the girl was in <placeName>District of Col.</placeName> <date when="1862-04-16">16 Apl</date>.</p>
                    <ab>child was bought of same est as my father bought mother</ab>
                    <ab>no doubt she belonged to <persName>J Thos Davis</persName>.</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="testimony">
                    <p><persName>Lucy Berry</persName> (<choice><abbr>cold</abbr><expan>colored</expan></choice>) This is my child. belonged to Mr <persName>Davis</persName> at time of Emancipation. lived with me never out of <placeName>District</placeName>. Mr <persName>Davis</persName> knew she was with me. sent for her last fall and I took her home.</p>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 type="procedural">
                    <ab><choice><abbr>Cert</abbr><expan>Certificate</expan></choice> ordered</ab>
                </div2>
                
                <pb xml:id="leaf002v" facs="cww.01005.004.jpg"/>                
               
                <div2 type="cover">
                    <ab><persName>Mary Bell</persName></ab>
                    <ab><date when="1862-09-03">Septr 3, 1862</date></ab>
                </div2>
            </div1>            
